The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Airtel net jumps 79% to Rs 934 cr

 OUR CORRESPONDENT

Mittal: Upbeat

 New Delhi, Oct. 27: Sunil Bharti Mittal-promoted Bharti Airtel today posted a 79 per cent increase in net profit at Rs 934 crore for the quarter ended September 30 against Rs 521 crore in the corresponding period in 2005-06.

 Total revenue rose to Rs 4,357 crore during the period July-September, registering a growth of 61 per cent compared with the same quarter last year, a company statement said.

 For the half year ended September 30, the company reported revenues of Rs 8,214 crore, up 57 per cent from the same period last year.

 The cash profit from operations grew 75 per cent to Rs 1,644 crore.

 Net profit for the first half of the current financial year surged 64 per cent to Rs 1,689 crore on a year-on-year basis.

 The company added 41.1 lakh customers in the second quarter this year, the highest ever, and reported a growth of 90 per cent year-on-year in customer additions.

 The company said its total subscriber base was 2.86 crore, enjoying a share of 21.4 per cent share of the total mobile market.

 This quarter, for the first time ever, Indias mobile net additions surpassed those of China. Wireless services continue to drive the growth of telecom services across the country with over 12.6 crore subscribers, said Sunil Bharti Mittal, CMD, Bharti Airtel Limited.

 India is in the midst of a wireless services boom as it adds upwards of 60 lakh new mobile customers roughly equal to the population of Israel each month.




